title: Stowaways found in refrigerated container bound for UK
content: At least 26 stowaways are found in a refrigerated container on a ferry bound to the UK from the Netherlands.

title: President Trump dismisses speculation about his health
content: President Donald Trump criticises the media speculation of his visit on Saturday.

title: US policy shift reduces chances of Mid-East peace deal
content: The way forward is even less clear after the Trump administration's move, says Barbara Plett Usher.

title: Chile protests: Thousands clash with police
content: Thousands of demonstrators took to the streets of Santiago as unrest entered a second month.

title: Julian Assange: Sweden drops rape investigation
content: Prosecutors drop a rape inquiry into Wikileaks founder Julian Assange, who is in custody in the UK.

title: Jeffrey Epstein guards charged with falsifying records
content: The two were responsible for watching over Epstein in prison on the night he killed himself.

title: A million faulty condoms recalled in Uganda
content: Some of the male contraceptives supplied by charity Marie Stopes contained holes or risked bursting.

title: Iran protests: UN fears dozens of people have been killed
content: Some sources have indicated about 200 people may have died since the protests erupted on Friday.

title: Hong Kong Polytechnic University: Protesters still inside as standoff continues
content: The standoff is into a third day, but younger protesters have been allowed to leave without arrest.

title: Spain starts tracking mobiles but denies spying
content: Millions of phone users are being followed this week but critics fear it is a step closer to spying.
